comments: Tucker (PHI) brings his hands toward LaVine (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as Tucker (PHI) releases away to roll.
DeRozan (CHI) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Harden's (PHI) arm after the release.
Williams (CHI) firms up in Harden's (PHI) path and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Vucevic (CHI) firms up in Harden's (PHI) path and absorbs the incidental body contact while setting the pick.
Embiid (PHI) avoids making arm contact with Vucevic (CHI) during the pursuit of the rebound.
Embiid (PHI) extends his leg during the jump shot attempt but any contact with Vucevic (CHI) is marginal.
Vucevic (CHI) firms up in a screening position in Maxey's (PHI) path and does not deliver contact.
Embiid (PHI) grabs Vucevic (CHI) during the drive, affecting his SQBR.
Williams (CHI) moves into Embiid (PHI) and dislodges him from his screening position.
Harden (PHI) engages and disengages with Lavine (CHI) as Lavine moves to set the pick.
Harden (PHI) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball as DeRozan (CHI) goes to make the pass.  As he drifts backwards, incidental contact occurs between him and Tucker (PHI).
Caruso (CHI) initiates contact with Harden's (PHI) head and affects his balance as he controls the rebound.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in LaVine's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs as both players meet during the pick.
Embiid (PHI) brings his hands toward LaVine (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as Embiid (PHI) releases away to roll.
Embiid (PHI) briefly brings his left hand toward Caruso (CHI) and releases away as he sets the pick.
Tucker (PHI) briefly places his hands on DeRozan's (CHI) back but the contact is marginal.
Embiid (PHI) jumps vertically and absorbs the ensuing contact with DeRozan (CHI) during his driving shot attempt.

DeRozan (CHI) brings his off-arm toward Embiid's (PHI) face and marginal contact occurs while defending the driving shot attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
LaVine (CHI) extends his left arm and initiates contact with Harris' (PHI) arm that affects Harris' SQBR.
Harris (PHI) contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt and incidental contact occurs as both players' hands meet after the release.
